The Bauchi State chapter of All Progressives Congress (APC) has promised to defeat its members who defected from the party to the Peoples Democratic Party (PDP) and other opposition parties. This was the message at the Bauchi-Central zonal solidarity rally to reiterate support for President Muhammadu Buhari and Governor Mohammed Abubakar, held in Misau, headquarters of Misau Local Government Area of the state. Bauchi-central zone consists of Misau, Dambam, Ganjuwa, Darazo, Ningi and Warji local government areas. It would be recalled that the senator representing Bauchi-Central,Â  Isah Hamma Misau, recently defected to the PDP. Other elected members from the zone that defected include; Salisu Zakari Ningi, the member representing, Ningi/Warji federal constituency in the House of Representatives. Speaking, the state APC chairman, Alhaji Uba Ahmed Nana, said that the party will remain united to confront challenges. He alleged that plans had been perfected by the opposition and other bad eggs to destabilise the party ahead of the 2019 general elections.